## Building a Multi-select Dropdown in Vue 3

**Mental model:** A multi-select is a toggleable panel of checkable options; the selection is an array (membership checked via `includes`). The trigger summarizes it; clicking an option toggles membership; an outside-click closes it. Controlled via `v-model`.

### Step 1 — Open state + v-model selection
```vue
<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';
const props = defineProps({ options: Array, modelValue: { type: Array, default: () => [] } });
const emit = defineEmits(['update:modelValue']);
const open = ref(false);
</script>
```

### Step 2 — Toggle membership
```js
function toggle(v) {
  const set = new Set(props.modelValue);
  set.has(v) ? set.delete(v) : set.add(v);
  emit('update:modelValue', [...set]);
}
```

### Step 3 — Close on outside click
Use a template ref on the root + a document `mousedown` listener.

```js
onMounted(() => document.addEventListener('mousedown', onDoc));
onUnmounted(() => document.removeEventListener('mousedown', onDoc));
function onDoc(e) { if (root.value && !root.value.contains(e.target)) open.value = false; }
```

### Step 4 — Summarize the trigger
```vue
<button>{{ modelValue.length ? modelValue.length + ' selected' : 'Select…' }}</button>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Click inside | `contains` check keeps it open. |
| Clear all | Emit `[]`. |
| Cleanup | Remove the doc listener in `onUnmounted`. |

**Interview tip:** Outside-click close = template `ref` on the root + a `document` `mousedown` listener with a `contains` check, removed in `onUnmounted` — the same recipe powers every popover, so name it as reusable.

